criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  amnestic mild cognitive impairment based on pre-screening evaluation;

          -  age 60-90 years;

          -  blood and urine chemistries indicative of normal renal, liver, thyroid and adrenal
             function;

          -  estimated GFR using the MDRD prediction equation must be >60 ml/min/1.73 m2;

          -  nonsmoker;

          -  MMSE score >24 at time of initial consent;

          -  suitable temporal window for cerebrovascular assessments.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  major psychiatric disorder (e.g. schizophrenia, bipolar disorder, major depression
             within past two years);

          -  neurological or autoimmune conditions affecting cognition (e.g. Parkinson's disease,
             epilepsy, multiple sclerosis, head trauma with loss of consciousness greater than 30
             min, large vessel infarct);

          -  systemic medical illnesses (e.g. cardiovascular disease, cancer, renal failure);

          -  substance abuse or dependence (DSM-V criteria);

          -  a Hachinski score greater than 4 (i.e. ruling out significant white matter disease);

          -  current medication use likely to affect CNS functions (e.g. long active
             benzodiazepines);

          -  claustrophobia, metal implants, pacemaker or other factors affecting feasibility
             and/or safety of MRI scanning*

          -  current smoking (including marijuana) within the past 3 months
